---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Novels" description="Serialized fiction at the intersection of AI governance, management, and organizational decision-making.">
  <style>
    .page-header { padding: clamp(4rem,8vw,6rem) clamp(1.5rem,5vw,5rem) 3rem; border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border); animation: fadeUp 0.6s ease forwards; }
    .page-kicker { font-size: 0.62rem; letter-spacing: 0.22em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 1.25rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; }
    .page-kicker::before { content: ''; width: 24px; height: 1px; background: var(--gold-dim); display: block; }
    .page-title { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(3rem,6vw,5rem); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1; color: var(--text-primary); letter-spacing: -0.02em; margin-bottom: 1.25rem; }
    .page-desc { font-size: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; max-width: 600px; }
    .section-label { font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.2em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 2rem; display: flex; align-items: center; gap: 1rem; }
    .section-label::after { content: ''; flex: 1; height: 1px; background: var(--border-light); }
    .novel-featured { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 220px 1fr; gap: 3rem; background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 3rem; margin-bottom: 2rem; cursor: pointer; transition: border-color 0.25s, background 0.25s; position: relative; overflow: hidden; text-decoration: none; color: inherit; }
    .novel-featured::before { content: ''; position: absolute; top: 0; left: 0; right: 0; height: 2px; background: linear-gradient(90deg, var(--gold), transparent); }
    .novel-featured:hover { border-color: var(--gold-dim); background: var(--bg-card-hover); }
    .cover-col { display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center; }
    .cover-col img { width: 180px; display: block; box-shadow: 14px 14px 0 rgba(0,0,0,0.5); transition: transform 0.3s; }
    .novel-featured:hover .cover-col img { transform: translateY(-4px); }
    .novel-status { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 6px; font-size: 0.6rem; letter-spacing: 0.18em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .novel-status::before { content: ''; width: 6px; height: 6px; background: var(--gold); border-radius: 50%; display: block; animation: pulse 2s infinite; }
    @keyframes pulse { 0%,100%{opacity:1}50%{opacity:0.4} }
    .novel-detail h2 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: clamp(1.8rem,3.5vw,2.8rem); font-weight: 300; line-height: 1.1; color: var(--text-primary); letter-spacing: -0.01em; }
    .novel-detail .subtitle { font-family: var(--serif); font-style: italic; font-size: 1.1rem; color: var(--gold); line-height: 1.4; margin: 0.4rem 0 1rem; }
    .novel-detail p { font-size: 0.9rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.8; max-width: 520px; }
    .novel-stats { display: flex; gap: 2rem; margin-top: 1.5rem; padding-top: 1.25rem; border-top: 1px solid var(--border); }
    .stat .num { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 300; color: var(--text-primary); line-height: 1; display: block; margin-bottom: 2px; }
    .stat .lbl { font-size: 0.62rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); }
    .read-cta { display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 10px; font-size: 0.72rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--gold); border-bottom: 1px solid var(--gold-dim); padding-bottom: 3px; transition: gap 0.2s; margin-top: 1rem; width: fit-content; }
    .novel-featured:hover .read-cta { gap: 16px; }
    .coming-grid { display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3,1fr); gap: 1.5rem; margin-top: 2rem; }
    .coming-card { background: var(--bg-card); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 2rem; opacity: 0.5; position: relative; overflow: hidden; }
    .coming-card::after { content: 'Forthcoming'; position: absolute; top: 1rem; right: 1rem; font-size: 0.55rem; letter-spacing: 0.16em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); border: 1px solid var(--border); padding: 2px 7px; border-radius: 1px; }
    .coming-spine { position: absolute; left: 0; top: 0; bottom: 0; width: 3px; }
    .coming-card .num { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 4rem; font-weight: 300; color: var(--text-muted); opacity: 0.2; line-height: 1; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .coming-card h3 { font-family: var(--serif); font-size: 1.3rem; font-weight: 400; color: var(--text-primary); margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .coming-card .author { font-size: 0.65rem; letter-spacing: 0.14em; text-transform: uppercase; color: var(--text-muted); margin-bottom: 0.75rem; }
    .coming-card p { font-size: 0.82rem; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.7; }
    @media(max-width:860px){.novel-featured{grid-template-columns:1fr;}.cover-col{display:none;}.coming-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;}}
    @media(max-width:600px){.coming-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr;}}
  </style>

  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="page-kicker">Management Fiction</div>
    <h1 class="page-title">Management Fiction</h1>
    <p class="page-desc">Fiction at the intersection of AI governance, management, and the human systems behind institutional decision-making. Published in chapters as they are written.</p>
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div style="padding:4rem 0;">
      <div class="section-label">Now Publishing</div>

      <a href="/novels/architecture-of-thinking" class="novel-featured">
        <div class="cover-col">
          <img src="/architecture-cover.png" alt="The Architecture of Thinking">
        </div>
        <div class="novel-detail">
          <div class="novel-status">Actively Publishing</div>
          <h2>The Architecture of Thinking</h2>
          <div class="subtitle">On Judgment, Machines, and Reasoning</div>
          <p>A leader navigating the intersection of technology, risk, and organizational decision-making discovers that the hardest questions about intelligent systems are not technical — they are institutional, ethical, and deeply human.</p>
          <div class="novel-stats">
            <div class="stat"><span class="num">8</span><span class="lbl">Chapters published</span></div>
            <div class="stat"><span class="num">~175</span><span class="lbl">Min total reading</span></div>
            <div class="stat"><span class="num">2025</span><span class="lbl">Series begun</span></div>
          </div>
          <div class="read-cta">Begin reading &rarr;</div>
        </div>
      </a>

      <div class="section-label" style="margin-top:3rem;">Forthcoming</div>
      <div class="coming-grid">
        <div class="coming-card"><div class="coming-spine" style="background:var(--blue-accent);"></div><div class="num">02</div><div class="author">Coming Soon</div><h3>Sovereign Signal</h3><p>Set in 2031 Brussels, a policy analyst discovers three major AI governance bodies running on the same foundation model.</p></div>
        <div class="coming-card"><div class="coming-spine" style="background:#3d6b30;"></div><div class="num">03</div><div class="author">Coming Soon</div><h3>The Integration Memo</h3><p>When a Fortune 100 CHRO mandates AI-assisted performance reviews, a mid-level manager must navigate the consequences.</p></div>
        <div class="coming-card"><div class="coming-spine" style="background:#7a5d9a;"></div><div class="num">04</div><div class="author">Open</div><h3>Your Novel Here</h3><p>Axiom Review publishes long-form fiction on AI governance, management, and organizational systems.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
